11#ifndef MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_SENDER_H_
12#define MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_SENDER_H_
13
14#include <map>
15#include <memory>
16#include <string>
17#include <utility>
18#include <vector>
19
20#include "absl/strings/string_view.h"
21#include "absl/types/optional.h"
22#include "api/array_view.h"
23#include "api/call/transport.h"
24#include "api/transport/webrtc_key_value_config.h"
25#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/include/flexfec_sender.h"
26#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/include/rtp_header_extension_map.h"
27#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/include/rtp_packet_sender.h"
28#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/include/rtp_rtcp_defines.h"
29#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/source/packet_sequencer.h"
30#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/source/rtp_packet_history.h"
31#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/source/rtp_rtcp_config.h"
32#include "modules/rtp_rtcp/source/rtp_rtcp_interface.h"
33#include "rtc_base/random.h"
34#include "rtc_base/rate_statistics.h"
35#include "rtc_base/synchronization/mutex.h"
36#include "rtc_base/thread_annotations.h"
37
38namespace webrtc {
39
40class FrameEncryptorInterface;
41class RateLimiter;
42class RtcEventLog;
43class RtpPacketToSend;
44
45class RTPSender {
46 public:
47 RTPSender(const RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration& config,
48 RtpPacketHistory* packet_history,
49 RtpPacketSender* packet_sender);
50
51 RTPSender() = delete;
52 RTPSender(const RTPSender&) = delete;
53 RTPSender& operator=(const RTPSender&) = delete;
54
55 ~RTPSender();
56
57 void SetSendingMediaStatus(bool enabled) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
58 bool SendingMedia() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
59 bool IsAudioConfigured() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
60
61 uint32_t TimestampOffset() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
62 void SetTimestampOffset(uint32_t timestamp) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
63
64 void SetRid(const std::string& rid) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
65
66 void SetMid(const std::string& mid) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
67
68 uint16_t SequenceNumber() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
69 void SetSequenceNumber(uint16_t seq) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
70
71 void SetCsrcs(const std::vector<uint32_t>& csrcs)
72 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
73
74 void SetMaxRtpPacketSize(size_t max_packet_size)
75 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
76
77 void SetExtmapAllowMixed(bool extmap_allow_mixed)
78 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
79
80 // RTP header extension
81 bool RegisterRtpHeaderExtension(absl::string_view uri, int id)
82 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
83 bool IsRtpHeaderExtensionRegistered(RTPExtensionType type) const
84 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
85 int32_t DeregisterRtpHeaderExtension(RTPExtensionType type)
86 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
87 void DeregisterRtpHeaderExtension(absl::string_view uri)
88 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
89
90 bool SupportsPadding() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
91 bool SupportsRtxPayloadPadding() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
92
93 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> GeneratePadding(
94 size_t target_size_bytes,
95 bool media_has_been_sent) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
96
97 // NACK.
98 void OnReceivedNack(const std::vector<uint16_t>& nack_sequence_numbers,
99 int64_t avg_rtt) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
100
101 int32_t ReSendPacket(uint16_t packet_id) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
102
103 // ACK.
104 void OnReceivedAckOnSsrc(int64_t extended_highest_sequence_number)
105 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
106 void OnReceivedAckOnRtxSsrc(int64_t extended_highest_sequence_number)
107 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
108
109 // RTX.
110 void SetRtxStatus(int mode) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
111 int RtxStatus() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
112 absl::optional<uint32_t> RtxSsrc() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_) {
113 return rtx_ssrc_;
114 }
115
116 void SetRtxPayloadType(int payload_type, int associated_payload_type)
117 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
118
119 // Size info for header extensions used by FEC packets.
120 static rtc::ArrayView<const RtpExtensionSize> FecExtensionSizes()
121 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
122
123 // Size info for header extensions used by video packets.
124 static rtc::ArrayView<const RtpExtensionSize> VideoExtensionSizes()
125 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
126
127 // Size info for header extensions used by audio packets.
128 static rtc::ArrayView<const RtpExtensionSize> AudioExtensionSizes()
129 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
130
131 // Create empty packet, fills ssrc, csrcs and reserve place for header
132 // extensions RtpSender updates before sending.
133 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> AllocatePacket() const
134 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
135 // Allocate sequence number for provided packet.
136 // Save packet's fields to generate padding that doesn't break media stream.
137 // Return false if sending was turned off.
138 bool AssignSequenceNumber(RtpPacketToSend* packet)
139 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
140 // Same as AssignSequenceNumber(), but applies sequence numbers atomically to
141 // a batch of packets.
142 bool AssignSequenceNumbersAndStoreLastPacketState(
143 rtc::ArrayView<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets)
144 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
145 // Maximum header overhead per fec/padding packet.
146 size_t FecOrPaddingPacketMaxRtpHeaderLength() const
147 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
148 // Expected header overhead per media packet.
149 size_t ExpectedPerPacketOverhead() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
150 // Including RTP headers.
151 size_t MaxRtpPacketSize() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
152
153 uint32_t SSRC() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_) { return ssrc_; }
154
155 absl::optional<uint32_t> FlexfecSsrc() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_) {
156 return flexfec_ssrc_;
157 }
158
159 // Sends packet to |transport_| or to the pacer, depending on configuration.
160 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/XXX): Remove in favor of EnqueuePackets().
161 bool SendToNetwork(std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet)
162 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
163
164 // Pass a set of packets to RtpPacketSender instance, for paced or immediate
165 // sending to the network.
166 void EnqueuePackets(std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets)
167 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
168
169 void SetRtpState(const RtpState& rtp_state) RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
170 RtpState GetRtpState() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
171 void SetRtxRtpState(const RtpState& rtp_state)
172 RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
173 RtpState GetRtxRtpState() const RTC_LOCKS_EXCLUDED(send_mutex_);
174
175 private:
176 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> BuildRtxPacket(
177 const RtpPacketToSend& packet);
178
179 bool IsFecPacket(const RtpPacketToSend& packet) const;
180
181 void UpdateHeaderSizes() RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(send_mutex_);
182
183 void UpdateLastPacketState(const RtpPacketToSend& packet)
184 RTC_EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(send_mutex_);
185
186 Clock* const clock_;
187 Random random_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
188
189 const bool audio_configured_;
190
191 const uint32_t ssrc_;
192 const absl::optional<uint32_t> rtx_ssrc_;
193 const absl::optional<uint32_t> flexfec_ssrc_;
194 // Limits GeneratePadding() outcome to <=
195 // |max_padding_size_factor_| * |target_size_bytes|
196 const double max_padding_size_factor_;
197
198 RtpPacketHistory* const packet_history_;
199 RtpPacketSender* const paced_sender_;
200
201 mutable Mutex send_mutex_;
202
203 bool sending_media_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
204 size_t max_packet_size_;
205
206 RtpHeaderExtensionMap rtp_header_extension_map_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
207 size_t max_media_packet_header_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
208 size_t max_padding_fec_packet_header_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
209
210 // RTP variables
211 uint32_t timestamp_offset_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
212 PacketSequencer sequencer_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
213 // RID value to send in the RID or RepairedRID header extension.
214 std::string rid_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
215 // MID value to send in the MID header extension.
216 std::string mid_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
217 // Should we send MID/RID even when ACKed? (see below).
218 const bool always_send_mid_and_rid_;
219 // Track if any ACK has been received on the SSRC and RTX SSRC to indicate
220 // when to stop sending the MID and RID header extensions.
221 bool ssrc_has_acked_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
222 bool rtx_ssrc_has_acked_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
223 std::vector<uint32_t> csrcs_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
224 int rtx_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
225 // Mapping rtx_payload_type_map_[associated] = rtx.
226 std::map<int8_t, int8_t> rtx_payload_type_map_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
227 bool supports_bwe_extension_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(send_mutex_);
228
229 RateLimiter* const retransmission_rate_limiter_;
230};
231
232} // namespace webrtc
233
234#endif // MODULES_RTP_RTCP_SOURCE_RTP_SENDER_H_
